result.execSummary:
Maureen N Villiers was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Maureen N Villiers was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Attorney Valeria Lenise Taylor in court after case was called.  James C. Griffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant has been extradited.   On motion of the State, Court ordered case dismissed.

Defendant Maureen N Villiers in court with attorney Valeria Lenise Taylor.  Defendant Maureen N Villiers in custody.  James C. Griffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Parties have received Governor's warrant and defendant is now waiting extradition.   Court ordered case adjourned for status conference in Branch 26.  Status conference scheduled for June 25, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Maureen N Villiers in court with attorney Mary Garvin Guimont.  Defendant Maureen N Villiers in custody.  Carole Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk:  bm
  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Pocan, Branch 26.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of rights and right to file a Writ of Habeas Corpus.  Court found the defendant is the person wanted in the State of Texas.  Defendant contested extradition.  Court ordered Defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  Defendant wants hearing on the next date.  Status conference scheduled for June 11, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
